reviews.review:
I have been playing this game for years. Some periods I played with full group of friends, some period I have played alone, some period just played survivor, some period just played killer. 
BHVR has been changing this game a lot since it's release, I saw perks being changed, game mechanics changing as well, good content being added, and so several bugs appearing and never going away too. BHVR has a HUGE team of devs, i 100% expected the game to be more balanced, to have the community happier about the way the game has been changing, but it is not exactly how we feel about DBD.

What to expect by playing this game:

- non balanced gameplay experience;
- very slow fixes for what the community mostly complaint about;
- Bugs that remains for years;
- Horn3 community that sometimes acts very toxic;
- Some horror related content is added often and for what I consider fair price those days, you also can get it with in-game currency;

All that said, I do still enjoy playing DBD, it is a way better when you have 4 other friends who play it as well so you can play the custom matches. 
If you are a solo player, I advise you to make friendship with people who you often see playing matches on your region, even if you do not want to use discord,  playing with someone you know will co-op with you, makes you feel a LOT better and enjoying a lot more.  

The game and it's content quite often get discounts on steam. Has been added free for some time on epic store too, for limited time. (๑˘︶˘๑)
